						Section 2 - Black: Book 7: Chapter 3: Verse 1
					-
						-
							They go swiftly in that it is the tenth day. In that it is the tenth
							day they loosen their sins. He who among men going swiftly falls in
							with a trackless way, he who strikes a post, and he who stumbles, are
							left out. So he, who on this tenth day, the Avivakya, comes to grief,
							is left out. If one points out (an error) to one who comes to grief, he
							seizes hold of him and comes out successfully, and then the one who
							pointed out (his error) is left out should point out (his error). If
							there be none there, then (the error) should be pointed out from within
							the Sadas. If there be none there, then it should be pointed out by the
							Grhapati. At any rate it should be pointed out. They sing the verses of
							the serpent queen on that day. The queen of what creeps is this
							(earth). Whatever on this (earth) they praise, whatever they have
							praised, through that is this (earth) the serpent queen. Now whatever
							they have praised with speech and what they will praise thereafter, (it
							is done thinking), 'Having won both and obtained them, let us stop.'
