							Brhaspati desired, 'May the gods have faith in me, and may I become
							their Purohita.' He saw this (rite) of twenty-four nights; he grasped
							it, and sacrificed with it. Then the gods had faith in him, and he
							became their Purohita. In those who knowing thus perform the twenty
							four night (rite) men have faith, and they become their Purohitas.
							There are the three days Jyotis, Go, and Ayus. The Jyotis is this
							(earth), the Go the atmosphere, and the Ayus yonder (sky) proceed;
							verily also in them they find support. These indeed are the quick paths
							of the sacrifice; verily by them do they proceed to the world of
							heaven. (The rite is one) of twenty-four nights. Twenty four
							half-months make up the year; the year is the world of heaven; verily
							they find support in the year, the world of heaven. Now the Gayatri is
							of twenty-four syllables; the Gayatri is splendour; verily by the
							Gayatri they win splendour. There are Atiratras on either side, to
							secure splendour.
						-
